@wbae1340 The Star Wars Prequels are flawed movies, not garbage movies. While yes, the acting, dialogue, line delivery, and characterization are often lacking, many of its themes still hold up. The dangers of unchecked corporations, politicians being apathetic to their citizens’ plights, and trading liberty for security are arguably more relevant today than they were when those movies were released. Although not inherently deep, it at least has something to say about societal issues instead of just trying to make more money like the Sequels. Furthermore, it laid the foundation for future stories to develop. It gave us some of the best content in the entire franchise with the Clone Wars Multi Media Project, Plagues and Darth Bane novels, and indirectly Kotor. In short, the Prequels had good ideas but just had bad execution.

The Sequels on the other hand are garbage movies. Not only does it share much of the same flaws as the Prequels, it even adds its very own. The entire conflict of the Original Trilogy is now pointless, given that what the Rebellion strived to build towards, the New Republic, dies from a third Death Star that they were too corrupt and stupid to notice. Luke’s journey and the story of the Jedi are also pointless in that it all gets thrown away over a bad dream Luke had. And for what? Just so the status quo can go back to square one because Disney Lucasfilm cannot come up with an original take on Star Wars. The Sequels have absolutely nothing to say about society, except that “selling weapons to bad is bad” or that abysmal “This is how we win” line the movie invalidates a second later, then contradicts with a lore breaking scene. And speaking of lore, that only amounts to whatever Disney Wars program wants it to be at any given moment. The Sequels can not even work as a trilogy as each film ignores and contradicts the previous one (along with the rest of the franchise). They even lack a main antagonist to drive their poor excuse of a plot along. In short, the Sequels have both bad ideas and execution.

Stop looking to RLM for takes on Star Wars, their takes and the effect they had on the franchise is what is garbage!

